#    ‚ĖĎ‚ĖÄ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ‚ĖÄ‚ĖÄ‚ĖÄ‚ĖĎ‚ĖÄ‚ĖÄ‚ĖÄ‚ĖĎ‚ĖÄ‚ĖĎ‚ĖÄ‚ĖĎ‚ĖÄ‚ĖĎ‚ĖĎ

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# File Purpose
#   Finds a file recursively and navigates (cd) to its parent directory.
#
# Problems Solved
#   - Navigating to a deep path when you only recall a specific filename inside it.
#   - Eliminates the need to `find ...`, copy path, paste, delete filename, then `cd`.
#
# Features
#   - **Smart Search:** Prefers `fd` (fast, respects gitignore) over `find`.
#   - **Content Preview:** Shows the file contents so you know you found the right one.
#   - **One-Key Edit:** Includes a binding (Ctrl-E) to open the file instead of jumping.
#
# Usage
#   - `fjump`        : Search from current directory.
#   - `fjump /var`   : Search inside /var.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Environment Sandbox
emulate -L zsh
setopt localoptions no_xtrace pipefail

local start_dir="${1:-.}"
local selected_file
local preview_cmd

# 2. Preview Strategy (Bat > Cat)
if (( $+commands[bat] )); then
    # Bat: Syntax highlighting, line numbers
    preview_cmd="bat --style=numbers --color=always --line-range :500 {} 2>/dev/null"
else
    # Fallback: Standard cat
    preview_cmd="cat {} 2>/dev/null"
fi

# 3. Search & Select
# We define the FZF interaction here. Note the addition of the 'ctrl-e' binding
# which allows you to pivot and edit the file instead of jumping to the folder.

# CASE A: Fast Search (fd)
if (( $+commands[fd] )); then
    selected_file=$(fd --type f --hidden --follow --exclude .git . "$start_dir" | \
        fzf \
        --no-multi \
        --prompt="ūüďć Jump to Parent > " \
        --header="Enter: CD to folder ‚ÄĘ Ctrl-E: Edit file" \
        --preview-window="right:60%:wrap:nohidden" \
        --preview "$preview_cmd" \
        --bind "ctrl-e:execute(${EDITOR:-vim} {})+abort"
    )

# CASE B: Universal Search (find)
else
    selected_file=$(find "$start_dir" -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' 2>/dev/null | \
        fzf \
        --no-multi \
        --prompt="ūüďć Jump to Parent > " \
        --header="Enter: CD to folder ‚ÄĘ Ctrl-E: Edit file" \
        --preview-window="right:60%:wrap:nohidden" \
        --preview "$preview_cmd" \
        --bind "ctrl-e:execute(${EDITOR:-vim} {})+abort"
    )
fi

# 4. Action: Jump to Parent
if [[ -n "$selected_file" ]]; then
    # Extract directory path
    local parent_dir=$(dirname "$selected_file")

    # Check if we are already there to avoid unnecessary messages
    if [[ "$parent_dir" == "." || "$parent_dir" == "$PWD" ]]; then
        print "${COLOR[YELLOW]}‚ö†${COLOR[RESET]} You are already in the parent directory."
        return 0
    fi

    print "\n${COLOR[GREEN]}::${COLOR[RESET]} Jumping to %B$parent_dir${COLOR[RESET]}..."

    if builtin cd "$parent_dir"; then
        # Optional: List contents upon arrival
        # ls -F --color=auto
        return 0
    else
        print "${COLOR[RED]}[ERROR]${COLOR[RESET]} Could not change directory."
        return 1
    fi
fi
